tau-Lop library is a tool for automatizing the procedure of 
modeling and quantifying the cost of parallel algorithms using
the tau-Lop model.

Version: 1.0
Date: Feb. 6th, 2018
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

1) Installing the library:

1. ./configure
2. make
3. make install
4. make tests


--------------------------------------------------------------------------

2) tau-Lop model is deeply described in the following papers:

- Juan-Antonio Rico-Gallego, Alexey L. Lastovetsky, Juan Carlos Díaz Martín:
Model-Based Estimation of the Communication Cost of Hybrid Data-Parallel Applications on Heterogeneous Clusters. 
IEEE Trans. Parallel Distrib. Syst. 28(11): 3215-3228 (2017)

- Juan-Antonio Rico-Gallego, Juan Carlos Díaz Martín, Alexey L. Lastovetsky:
Extending τ-Lop to model concurrent MPI communications in multicore clusters. 
Future Generation Comp. Syst. 61: 66-82 (2016)

- Juan-Antonio Rico-Gallego, Juan Carlos Díaz Martín:
τ-Lop: Modeling performance of shared memory MPI. 
Parallel Computing 46: 14-31 (2015)


3) Visit http://hpc.unex.es/taulop for more information and elaborated examples.

